                            <comment id="14729024" author="robbinspg" created="Thu, 3 Sep 2015 13:23:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My pull request build for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-10431&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-10431&lt;/a&gt; failed with this error so I took a look. I think it&apos;s another timing issue where the assert on the progress listener occurs before the asynchronous notification thread has completed processing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Something like this should fix it:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;diff --git a/streaming/src/test/scala/org/apache/spark/streaming/InputStreamsSuite.scala b/streaming/src/test/scala/org/apache/spark/streaming/InputStreamsSuite.scala&lt;br/&gt;
index ec2852d..e27d315 100644&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#8212; a/streaming/src/test/scala/org/apache/spark/streaming/InputStreamsSuite.scala&lt;br/&gt;
+++ b/streaming/src/test/scala/org/apache/spark/streaming/InputStreamsSuite.scala&lt;br/&gt;
@@ -76,6 +76,8 @@&lt;br/&gt;
           fail(&quot;Timeout: cannot finish all batches in 30 seconds&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
         }&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+        ssc.scheduler.listenerBus.waitUntilEmpty(500)&lt;br/&gt;
+&lt;br/&gt;
         // Verify all &quot;InputInfo&quot;s have been reported&lt;br/&gt;
         assert(ssc.progressListener.numTotalReceivedRecords === input.size)&lt;br/&gt;
         assert(ssc.progressListener.numTotalProcessedRecords === input.size)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14729030" author="robbinspg" created="Thu, 3 Sep 2015 13:25:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;should I add this change to the PR for Spark-10431 or submit PR for this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
